data.title: Google’s most popular and least popular top level domains
data.meta_description: Just what are the most popular and the least popular top level domains?
data.text:
Sharing is caring!

What are the most popular top-level domains? At least, which are the ones that show up most on pages indexed in Google?

I wondered this yesterday after seeing a news article stating that the registration of .cn (china) top-level domain names topped 1 million for the first time by the end of 2005. The seed for my wonderment was probably planted by EGOL, at Cre8asite Forums, asking about using a .info top-level domain earlier that day.

So I decided to check to see the most popular top-level domains in Google since that was the easiest place to get some statistics.

I found a couple of lists of top-level domains (generic TLDs and country-code TLDs). I then searched for the number of results that appeared in Google, using the advanced “site” search operator and my TLD lists. So, for example, a search for “site:.com” without quotation marks might show me approximately how many pages appear in Google’s index that are on sites using a “.com” top-level domain.

I’ve listed the 20 most popular top-level domains, then the 20 least popular top-level domains, and finally, the whole list.

The 20 most popular top level domains with the most page results in Google:
